<UserControl xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="800" d:DesignHeight="450"
             x:Class="StellarMVVM_2024.Views.setting_goals_archive_screen">
	<UserControl.Styles>
		<StyleInclude Source="/Styles/archive info styles/making_decisions_archive_stylesheet.axaml"/>
	</UserControl.Styles>
	<Panel Background="Pink">
		<StackPanel
		HorizontalAlignment="Center"
		Name="settingGoalsArchiveStackPanel">
			<TextBlock
				Classes="title"
				PointerReleased="returnPrevious">
				setting goals
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				1. goals can be long-term or short-term
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				2. short-term goals include paying for a vacation, car maintenance, etc.
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				3. to set a goal, understand your inflow and your outflow. keep track of what you earn and spend
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				4. ensure to keep a realistic goal
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				5. short-term goals can be achieved in a year or less (any longer is a long-term goal)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				6. always remember to maintain an emergency fund in addition to the goal
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				7. a way to start goals is to start saving, like buying cheaper alternatives
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				8. put whatever you saved from your goal into an interest-bearing account
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				9.  the consider interest, inflation, and appreciation rates when planning a goal
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				10. goals can be long-term as well, like paying for a car, a house, or tuition
			</TextBlock>
		</StackPanel>
	</Panel>
</UserControl>
